					<description><![CDATA[<p>Win favor with the Instagram algorithm‚Äîand more importantly, your followers.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/09/27/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement">12 Easy &#038; Effective Ways to Increase Engagement on Instagram</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Marketers and business owners are constantly looking for ways to interact with their audience. With more than 1.4 million monthly active users (Source: <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/272014/global-social-networks-ranked-by-number-of-users/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Statista</a>), Instagram offers serious potential for building your brand. But you need more than just an account and an audience to experience the full potential of this platform.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/272014/global-social-networks-ranked-by-number-of-users/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-most-popular-social-media-platforms.png" alt="how to increase instagram engagement - most popular social media platforms worldwide" width="720" height="466" class="size-full wp-image-64893 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-most-popular-social-media-platforms.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-most-popular-social-media-platforms-480x311.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></a></p>
<p>You need engagement. Comments, shares, likes, saves, and other actions that show your content resonates with your audience.</p>
<p>In this post, we&#8217;re going to share 12 ways you can increase your Instagram engagement and build an emotional connection with your followers.</p>
<h2>Why does Instagram engagement matter?</h2>
<p>Instagram engagement is not about how many users are following you, but about how your followers interact with your posts. Engagement metrics include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Comments</li>
<li>Shares</li>
<li>Likes</li>
<li>Saves</li>
<li>Stories views</li>
<li>Interactions with stories stickers</li>
<li>Brand mentions</li>
<li>Link click-throughs</li>
<li>Direct Messages (DMs)</li>
</ul>
<p>Not only does high engagement indicate that your content resonates with your audience, but the Instagram algorithm also considers engagement when deciding what content to show users.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-get-more-engagement-on-instagram-algorithm.png" alt="how to increase engagement on instagram - algorithm ranking factors" width="720" height="387" class="size-full wp-image-64878 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-get-more-engagement-on-instagram-algorithm.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-get-more-engagement-on-instagram-algorithm-480x258.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>If your posts have high engagement, they&#8217;ll be more likely to appear in the feeds of users you consistently engage with, helping to increase your reach and brand awareness.</p>
<h2>How to increase engagement on Instagram</h2>
<p>Given<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/11/most-popular-social-media-platforms"> Instagram&#8217;s popularity</a>, successful social media marketers consider Instagram engagement a priority. Here‚Äôs how you can increase your Instagram engagement.</p>
<h3>1. Know your audience</h3>
<p>The first step in keeping your followers engaged is <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience">identifying your audience</a>. If you don‚Äôt know what intrigues and motivates them, you won‚Äôt know how to create content that engages them. Here&#8217;s how to do it:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Define your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/09/23/buyer-personas">buyer personas</a>.</strong> This is a clear representation of who your ideal customer is. What are their pain points and desires? What are their hobbies? What do they do for work? What&#8217;s their schedule like?</li>
<li><strong>Look at Instagram audience insights.</strong> Here you will find demographic information about your audience. Under the ‚Äú<strong>Insights</strong>‚Äù section, click ‚Äú<strong>Audience</strong>.‚Äù You‚Äôll find details about people interacting with your posts, including their location, age, and gender.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-engagement-on-instagram-audience-insights.png" alt="how to increase engagement on instagram - audience insights" width="720" height="533" class="size-full wp-image-64879 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-engagement-on-instagram-audience-insights.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-engagement-on-instagram-audience-insights-480x355.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Look at your competitors‚Äô profiles. </strong>Who likes and comments on their posts? What content are they sharing? How do they interact with their followers?</li>
<li><strong>Use social listening tools.</strong> This can help you track any mentions of your brand or products. See what people are saying and what they want you to address.</li>
</ul>
<h3>2. Use strong captions with CTAs</h3>
<p>Strong captions accomplish three things. They:</p>
<ul>
<li>Add context to the pictures in your post</li>
<li>Bring out your brand personality</li>
<li>Drive your audience to take an action</li>
</ul>
<p>That last one is key. After writing a <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/instagram-captions-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">catchy caption</a> on what the post is about and adding hashtags and emojis, it‚Äôs time to prompt them to take action. For example, ‚ÄúLet me know what you think in the comments‚Äù or &#8220;Click the link in our bio to learn more.&#8221;</p>
<p>Here‚Äôs a video of Honest Beauty‚Äôs founder, Jessica Alba. In the caption, the CTA prompts their audience to click the link on their bio to purchase the products.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/reel/Cis88IEjlj7/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-engagement-on-instagram-link-in-bio-caption.png" alt="how to increase instagram engagement - caption with CTA" width="600" height="535" class="size-full wp-image-64884 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-engagement-on-instagram-link-in-bio-caption.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-engagement-on-instagram-link-in-bio-caption-480x428.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.instagram.com/reel/Cis88IEjlj7/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Image source</a></em></p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><p>Speaking of CTAs&#8230;</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4d9.png" alt="üìô" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Free guide¬† <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite36CallToActionPhrases.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_36CallToActionPhrases_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&gt;&gt; The 36 Best Call to Action Phrases (Ever)</a></strong></p></div></div>
<h3>3. Engage your audience through creative interactive stickers</h3>
<p>Instagram has plenty of interactive story stickers you can use to drive engagement with your posts. You can use the stickers in different ways:</p>
<ul>
<li>Use the <strong>quiz sticker</strong> to ask your followers fun questions, including multiple-choice questions.</li>
<li>Use the <strong>music sticker</strong> to add soundtracks or lyrics to your stories. Be creative and match the song with the mood, such as cheerful music on a Monday motivation post or maybe a dramatic tone to a long-awaited announcement.</li>
<li>Use the <strong>poll sticker</strong> to ask for people&#8217;s opinions. It could be something like which packaging they prefer or which products they like more.</li>
<li>Ask for your followers‚Äô thoughts about something with the <strong>questions sticker</strong>. You can also prompt them to ask you about something. If you‚Äôre willing to open the floor, host an AMA (ask me anything).</li>
</ul>
<p>Stories stickers make your audience feel recognized and that their opinion matters. Every question asked or poll taken is one more engagement.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-instagram-engagement-stickers.png" alt="how to increase engagement on instagram - stories with stickers" width="600" height="493" class="size-full wp-image-64880 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-instagram-engagement-stickers.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-instagram-engagement-stickers-480x394.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Browse through even more <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/01/instagram-story-ideas">engaging Instagram Story ideas here</a>.</p>
<h3>4. Create interesting Instagram Stories &amp; Reels</h3>
<p>Who doesn‚Äôt love Instagram Reels, especially when they‚Äôre interesting? These short, entertaining videos are an excellent way for marketers and business owners to drive visibility and engagement to their pages.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/22/instagram-reels-ideas-for-businesses">Instagram Reels ideas</a> are endless: to share customer experiences, before-and-after videos, interactive how-to videos, and behind-the-scenes peeks.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-reel-example.webp"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-reel-example.webp" alt="how to increase instagram engagement - example of a reel" width="300" height="534" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-64885" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-reel-example.webp 300w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-reel-example-169x300.webp 169w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></p>
<p>You can also use our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/26/instagram-story-templates">Instagram Story templates</a> so you&#8217;re not starting from scratch!</p>
<h3>5. Use carousel posts to encourage more engagement</h3>
<p>According to <a href="https://www.socialinsider.io/blog/instagram-carousel-research/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Socialinsider</a>, of all Instagram post types, carousels have the highest engagement rate of <a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/instagram-carousels/379311/">1.92%</a> (and 2.33% when you use all 10 carousel slides).</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-rate-carousel-image-video.png" alt="how to increase engagement on instagram - engagement rate of post types" width="720" height="396" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-64886" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-rate-carousel-image-video.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-rate-carousel-image-video-480x264.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You can‚Äôt miss taking advantage of this to increase your engagement. There are many ways of using carousel posts‚Äîdon‚Äôt just pick any images and expect your followers to camp on it. Get creative and mix in videos to attract even more interaction. Use them for:</p>
<ul>
<li>User-generated content</li>
<li>Product tutorials</li>
<li>Multiple product views</li>
<li>Before and after photos</li>
<li>Your brand story</li>
<li>Customer reviews</li>
</ul>
<p>Canva hosts a weekly design challenge and uses carousel posts to display the highlights for the week&#8217;s theme.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement-carousel-post.jpg" alt="how to increase instagram engagement - example of a carousel post" width="600" height="389" class="size-full wp-image-64887 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement-carousel-post.jpg 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement-carousel-post-480x311.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CizTEnrN8gB/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Image source</a></em></p>
<p>Every carousel slide is a chance to drive engagement‚Äî10 opportunities in 1 post. Don‚Äôt miss out on yours.</p>
<h3>6. Create and post relatable memes</h3>
<p>An endless stream of perfect images and pristine products can become monotonous to your followers. Memes are more authentic and can attract your audience‚Äôs attention, especially if they‚Äôre relatable and resonate with your followers.</p>
<p>Like this one:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-tank-sinatra.png" alt="how to increase engagement on instagram - example of post with relatable meme" width="720" height="388" class="size-full wp-image-64881 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-tank-sinatra.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-tank-sinatra-480x259.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Followers are more likely to share, comment, and even repost them on their stories because they don‚Äôt feel like they‚Äôre sharing an ad. And who doesn‚Äôt want a good laugh anyway? So put on that meme lord (or lady) hat and enchant your brand‚Äôs way into your followers‚Äô hearts.</p>
<h3><span style="color: #666666; font-size: 14px;">Inspiring quotes and repurposed tweets are perfect for driving engagement.</span></h3>
<h3>7. Post valuable content regularly</h3>
<p>Sharing funny posts is great, but you shouldn‚Äôt forget to add value for your followers. Create unique content they can repeatedly reference or share with their circles. We have tons of <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/what-to-post-on-instagram/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram post ideas here</a>, but for starters:</p>
<ul>
<li>Helpful tips in eye-catching infographics</li>
<li>Graphs and charts to visualize data</li>
<li>Step-by-step tutorials</li>
<li>Creative ideas</li>
</ul>
<p>If you‚Äôre creating a carousel post with a step-by-step how-to guide, recipe, or a list of tips, include a ‚ÄúSave this Post‚Äù call to action. Encourage your followers to save it and come back later for reference.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement-useful-post-example.png" alt="how to increase engagement on instagram - example of a useful post" width="720" height="473" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-64882" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement-useful-post-example.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement-useful-post-example-480x315.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CiiPRZ_unRy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<h3>8. Host and collaborate with industry influencers</h3>
<p>Instagram is an interactive platform. What‚Äôs the point if you‚Äôre not engaging and interacting with other accounts?</p>
<p>Engaging with similar accounts expands your net and helps you reach potential followers. It‚Äôs even better when the other accounts are people with much bigger nets‚Äîindustry influencers. Influencers have loyal followings that can increase your visibility and introduce your brand to audiences that would have been otherwise hard to reach.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/03/21/social-media-influencers">Find influencers in your industry</a>, build a relationship with them, and then collaborate with them. Feature them in your posts, repost their content, and co-create content with them.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement-influencer-post.png" alt="how to increase instagram engagement - influencer post" width="600" height="386" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-64888" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement-influencer-post.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/how-to-increase-instagram-engagement-influencer-post-480x309.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Not only will they engage with these posts, but they&#8217;ll also share them with their own followers.¬† This will grant you broader coverage and help you <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/get-more-instagram-followers">attract more relevant followers</a> as well.</p>
<h3>9. Run Instagram lives</h3>
<p>Your Instagram followers want to see the face behind the account once in a while. And considering that <a href="https://livestream.com/blog/live-video-statistics-livestream" target="_blank" rel="noopener">82%</a> of followers prefer watching a live stream to reading social posts, why not try out Instagram live?</p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/04/30/instagram-live">Instagram live videos</a> give your followers a more immersive experience. They also get to meet and interact with you in a personal, engaging way.</p>
<p>Viewers can ask questions, share ideas, and leave comments in real time‚Äîa perfect way for your brand to engage with followers. If you‚Äôre wondering what types of content you can share on Instagram live, try;</p>
<ul>
<li>Q&amp;A sessions on your brand, products, or relevant topics.</li>
<li>Sneak peek sessions for a product you‚Äôre about to launch.</li>
<li>Discussions on current trends or events in your industry.</li>
<li>Customer support FAQs.</li>
<li>Learning sessions with industry influencers.</li>
</ul>
<p>Tap into the power of selling during live sessions with Instagram Live Shopping (one of our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/13/digital-marketing-trends-2022">digital marketing trends of this year</a>). With this feature, you can interact with your viewers and sell directly to them. Save your live videos so potential customers can shop for the featured products after the live stream.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-instagram-live-shopping.png" alt="how to increase instagram engagement - instagram live shopping post" width="600" height="610" class="size-full wp-image-64889 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-instagram-live-shopping.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-instagram-live-shopping-480x488.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>10. Use polls and questions to get feedback</h3>
<p>Want to know how your audience perceives your brand and products? <a href="http://localiq.com/blog/how-to-do-a-poll-on-instagram/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Create polls and questions on your Instagram stories</a>.</p>
<p>Polls, unlike contests, are easy to create using stickers. Plus, you don‚Äôt need a good reason to create one. Just think of a quick question to which you‚Äôd also be happy to respond.</p>
<p>Use polls to ask about preferences, would-you-rathers, favorites, and more.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-instagram-story-ideas-poll.jpeg" alt="how to increase engagement on instagram - story with poll" width="720" height="403" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-64890" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-instagram-story-ideas-poll.jpeg 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-instagram-engagement-instagram-story-ideas-poll-480x269.jpeg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /><a href="https://www.instagram.com/reel/CgzFWGaAFQy/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link"></a></p>
<h3>11. Leverage the power of hashtags</h3>
<p>If you‚Äôre not using<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/05/29/instagram-hashtags"> Instagram hashtags</a>, you‚Äôre missing out on a valuable opportunity to get your content into your potential followers‚Äô feeds. Hashtags help you to categorize your posts and get found by people when they&#8217;re exploring specific topics. This is a great way to get your content in front of the people most likely to engage with it‚Äîfollower or not.</p>
<p>Instagram allows you to use up to 30 hashtags, but don‚Äôt use all of them on every post. Stick with the ones that are most relevant to the post so you can attract a relevant audience to each one. One of the best ways to find hashtags is just to search them right in Insta:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-engagement-instagram-hashtag-search.png" alt="how to increase instagram engagement - example of a hashtag search" width="720" height="462" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-64891" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-engagement-instagram-hashtag-search.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/increase-engagement-instagram-hashtag-search-480x308.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>12. Post when your audience is most active</h3>
<p>Your memes may be hilarious and your content helpful, but if you post when your audience is asleep, well‚Ä¶if only there were a way for them to view from dreamland. But there isn‚Äôt. So, post when your audience is most active.</p>
<p>The <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/12/01/best-time-to-post-on-instagram">best time to post on Instagram</a> varies depending on your audience, location, and content type.</p>
